# SOC 2 Type II Security Checklist

This checklist covers the Trust Services Criteria for SOC 2 Type II compliance. Use this as a guide for preparing for your SOC 2 audit.

## Trust Services Criteria Overview

SOC 2 is based on five Trust Services Criteria:

1. **Security (CC)** - Common Criteria related to security [Required]
2. **Availability (A)** - System is available for operation and use
3. **Processing Integrity (PI)** - System processing is complete, valid, accurate, timely, and authorized
4. **Confidentiality (C)** - Information designated as confidential is protected
5. **Privacy (P)** - Personal information is collected, used, retained, disclosed, and disposed of properly

**Note:** Security is mandatory; the other four are optional based on your business needs.

---

## Common Criteria (CC) - Security

### CC1: Control Environment

#### CC1.1 - Organization demonstrates commitment to integrity and ethical values

- [ ] Code of conduct or ethics policy established
- [ ] Regular ethics training for all employees
- [ ] Whistleblower hotline or reporting mechanism
- [ ] Ethics violations are investigated and documented

#### CC1.2 - Board demonstrates independence and oversight

- [ ] Board or equivalent oversight body exists
- [ ] Regular board meetings scheduled (at least quarterly)
- [ ] Board reviews security and compliance matters
- [ ] Meeting minutes documented and retained

#### CC1.3 - Management establishes structures, authorities, and responsibilities

- [ ] Organizational chart documented
- [ ] Job descriptions include security responsibilities
- [ ] Security roles clearly defined (CISO, Security Team, etc.)
- [ ] Reporting structure documented

#### CC1.4 - Organization demonstrates commitment to competence

- [ ] Required competencies documented for each role
- [ ] Security awareness training program established
- [ ] Role-specific security training provided
- [ ] Training completion tracked and documented
- [ ] Annual security training refresher

#### CC1.5 - Organization holds individuals accountable

- [ ] Performance evaluations include security objectives
- [ ] Security incidents tracked to individuals
- [ ] Disciplinary actions documented
- [ ] Non-compliance consequences defined

### CC2: Communication and Information

#### CC2.1 - Information system relevant to security objectives

- [ ] System architecture documented
- [ ] Data flow diagrams created
- [ ] Critical systems identified
- [ ] Dependencies documented

#### CC2.2 - Communication with external parties

- [ ] Vendor security requirements documented
- [ ] Customer security commitments documented
- [ ] Security incident communication procedures
- [ ] Third-party risk assessment process

#### CC2.3 - Communication with internal parties

- [ ] Security policies communicated to all employees
- [ ] Security updates distributed regularly
- [ ] Incident reporting mechanism established
- [ ] Security team contact information available

### CC3: Risk Assessment

#### CC3.1 - Organization specifies objectives

- [ ] Security objectives documented
- [ ] Business objectives aligned with security
- [ ] Compliance requirements identified
- [ ] Objectives reviewed annually

#### CC3.2 - Organization identifies and analyzes risks

- [ ] Risk assessment performed at least annually
- [ ] Risk register maintained
- [ ] Risk likelihood and impact documented
- [ ] Risk owners assigned

#### CC3.3 - Organization considers potential for fraud

- [ ] Fraud risk assessment completed
- [ ] Fraud prevention controls implemented
- [ ] Fraud detection mechanisms in place
- [ ] Regular fraud risk reviews

#### CC3.4 - Organization identifies and assesses changes

- [ ] Change management process documented
- [ ] Security impact assessed for changes
- [ ] Changes to external environment monitored
- [ ] Business model changes reviewed for security impact

### CC4: Monitoring Activities

#### CC4.1 - Organization conducts ongoing and/or separate evaluations

- [ ] Continuous monitoring implemented
- [ ] Security metrics tracked
- [ ] Regular security reviews scheduled
- [ ] Internal audits performed
- [ ] Vulnerability assessments conducted

#### CC4.2 - Organization evaluates and communicates deficiencies

- [ ] Deficiency tracking system in place
- [ ] Remediation plans documented
- [ ] Deficiencies reported to management
- [ ] Remediation progress tracked

### CC5: Control Activities

#### CC5.1 - Organization selects and develops control activities

- [ ] Security controls documented
- [ ] Control objectives defined
- [ ] Controls mapped to risks
- [ ] Control effectiveness monitored

#### CC5.2 - Organization deploys controls through policies

- [ ] Security policies documented
- [ ] Policies approved by management
- [ ] Policies communicated to relevant parties
- [ ] Policy exceptions documented and approved

#### CC5.3 - Organization deploys controls through technology

- [ ] Security tools implemented
- [ ] Access controls configured
- [ ] Encryption implemented
- [ ] Security monitoring tools deployed

### CC6: Logical and Physical Access Controls

#### CC6.1 - Organization obtains or generates and uses relevant, quality information

- [ ] Access requirements documented
- [ ] Access requests logged
- [ ] Access decisions documented
- [ ] Access reviews performed quarterly

#### CC6.2 - Organization internally communicates information

- [ ] Access policies communicated
- [ ] Security training includes access control
- [ ] Access changes communicated promptly

#### CC6.3 - Organization communicates with external parties

- [ ] Vendor access requirements documented
- [ ] Customer access procedures documented
- [ ] Third-party access monitored

#### CC6.4 - Organization identifies and authenticates users

- [ ] Unique user IDs for all users
- [ ] Password complexity requirements enforced
- [ ] Multi-factor authentication (MFA) implemented
- [ ] MFA enforced for all privileged accounts
- [ ] Service accounts managed and monitored

#### CC6.5 - Organization considers multiple uses of credentials

- [ ] Single sign-on (SSO) implemented where appropriate
- [ ] Credential sharing prohibited
- [ ] Shared account usage documented and justified
- [ ] Regular review of shared accounts

#### CC6.6 - Organization manages access credentials

- [ ] Password policy enforced (complexity, length, expiration)
- [ ] Credentials securely stored (hashed, encrypted)
- [ ] Credential rotation process for service accounts
- [ ] Compromised credentials revoked immediately

#### CC6.7 - Organization restricts physical access

- [ ] Physical access controls at data center
- [ ] Visitor logs maintained
- [ ] Badge or key card access system
- [ ] Physical access reviews performed

#### CC6.8 - Organization restricts logical access

- [ ] Role-based access control (RBAC) implemented
- [ ] Least privilege principle enforced
- [ ] Segregation of duties implemented
- [ ] Access rights reviewed quarterly
- [ ] Terminated employee access revoked same day

### CC7: System Operations

#### CC7.1 - Organization detects and responds to security incidents

- [ ] Incident response plan documented
- [ ] Incident detection tools deployed
- [ ] Security monitoring 24/7 or business hours + alerts
- [ ] Incident response team identified
- [ ] Incident response testing performed annually

#### CC7.2 - Organization monitors system components

- [ ] System availability monitored
- [ ] Performance metrics tracked
- [ ] Capacity planning performed
- [ ] Alerts configured for critical issues

#### CC7.3 - Organization evaluates security events

- [ ] Security event logs collected
- [ ] Log analysis performed regularly
- [ ] Security event escalation process
- [ ] Log retention policy (at least 1 year)

#### CC7.4 - Organization responds to security incidents

- [ ] Incident response procedures documented
- [ ] Incident severity classification defined
- [ ] Escalation procedures documented
- [ ] Post-incident reviews conducted

#### CC7.5 - Organization identifies, develops, and deploys safeguards

- [ ] Security patches applied timely (critical within 30 days)
- [ ] Vulnerability management program
- [ ] Security advisories monitored
- [ ] Emergency patches process defined

### CC8: Change Management

#### CC8.1 - Organization authorizes, designs, develops, configures, documents, tests, approves, and implements changes

- [ ] Change management policy documented
- [ ] Change request process defined
- [ ] Change approval process established
- [ ] Testing procedures for changes
- [ ] Change documentation requirements
- [ ] Rollback procedures documented
- [ ] Emergency change procedures

### CC9: Risk Mitigation

#### CC9.1 - Organization identifies, selects, and develops risk mitigation activities

- [ ] Risk treatment plans documented
- [ ] Risk mitigation controls implemented
- [ ] Risk acceptance formally documented
- [ ] Residual risk assessed

#### CC9.2 - Organization assesses and manages risks with vendors

- [ ] Vendor risk assessment process
- [ ] Vendor security requirements documented
- [ ] Vendor security assessments performed
- [ ] Vendor contracts include security terms
- [ ] Vendor compliance monitored
- [ ] Vendor access tracked and audited

