## Additional Criteria (Optional)

### Availability (A1)

#### A1.1 - Organization maintains availability commitments

- [ ] Service Level Agreements (SLAs) defined
- [ ] Uptime targets documented
- [ ] Availability monitoring implemented
- [ ] Availability reports generated

#### A1.2 - Organization performs system monitoring

- [ ] System availability monitored
- [ ] Performance metrics tracked
- [ ] Capacity thresholds defined
- [ ] Proactive alerting configured

#### A1.3 - Organization manages system capacity

- [ ] Capacity planning performed
- [ ] Scalability plans documented
- [ ] Load testing performed
- [ ] Resource utilization monitored

### Processing Integrity (PI1)

#### PI1.1 - Organization achieves processing objectives

- [ ] Data validation controls implemented
- [ ] Error handling procedures documented
- [ ] Data accuracy verified
- [ ] Processing completeness verified

#### PI1.2 - Organization monitors processing

- [ ] Processing metrics tracked
- [ ] Data quality monitoring
- [ ] Transaction logging
- [ ] Reconciliation procedures

### Confidentiality (C1)

#### C1.1 - Organization identifies and maintains confidential information

- [ ] Data classification policy
- [ ] Confidential data identified
- [ ] Confidentiality requirements documented
- [ ] Data handling procedures

#### C1.2 - Organization disposes of confidential information

- [ ] Data retention policy documented
- [ ] Secure deletion procedures
- [ ] Media disposal procedures
- [ ] Disposal verification process

### Privacy (P1)

#### P1.1 - Organization provides notice and choice

- [ ] Privacy policy published
- [ ] Cookie consent implemented
- [ ] Data collection notice provided
- [ ] Opt-out mechanisms available

#### P1.2 - Organization collects personal information

- [ ] Data minimization principle applied
- [ ] Consent mechanisms implemented
- [ ] Purpose limitation documented
- [ ] Legal basis for processing documented

